column2: Systematic Phenotyping and Characterization of the 5xFAD mouse model of Alzheimer’s Disease

we conducted a detailed phenotypic characterization of the 5xFAD model on a congenic C57BL/6J strain background, across its lifespan – including a seldomly analyzed 18-month old time point to provide temporally correlated phenotyping of this model and a template for characterization of new models of LOAD as they are generated. This comprehensive analysis included quantification of plaque burden, Aβ biochemical levels, and neuropathology, neurophysiological measurements and behavioral and cognitive assessments, and evaluation of microglia, astrocytes, and neurons. Analysis of transcriptional changes was conducted using bulk-tissue generated RNA-seq data from microdissected cortices and hippocampi as a function of aging, which can be explored at the UCI Mouse Explorer and AD Knowledge Portal. This deep-phenotyping pipeline identified novel aspects of age-related pathology in the 5xFAD model.
Bulk RNA-seq of 4 different time point(4,8,12,18 month) in two brain regoins (hippocampus and cortex) and two strains (5xFAD and BL6)
Expression profiling by high throughput sequencing
